{
  "texts": [
    "A chooses a y ′ ⊑ y; 2.",
    "E chooses an x ′ ⊑ x; 3.",
    "A chooses an x ′′ ⊑ x ′; if R i (x ′′) = ∅, then A wins, otherwise play continues; 4.",
    "E chooses a y ′′ ∈ R i (x ′′); if y ′′ ≬ y ′, then E wins, otherwise A wins.One can think of A and E as arguing about whether y is accessible to x: if it is, then for any way y ′ of further specifying y, there should be some way x ′ of further specifying x that \"locks in\" access to states compatible with y ′, i.e., such that all refinements x ′′ of x ′ have access to some state y ′′ compatible with y ′.",
    "If refinements of x cannot keep up with refinements of y in this way, then y is not accessible to x."
  ]
}